<h1>Getting Started</h1>

<div class="text"> 

<p>
Make sure you have <a href="http://www.getfirefox.com">Firefox</a> installed
and then
install the <a href="index.jsp?content=firefox-extension">VIEW
Firefox toolbar add-on</a>.
</p>

<p>Restart Firefox to complete the installation.  When Firefox starts, you
should see a new VIEW toolbar.</p>

<div class="screenshot">
<img src="firefox-extension/toolbar-screenshot.png" alt="VIEW toolbar" />
</div>

<br />

<h2>Using VIEW</h2>

<p>
Choose a language, a topic, and an activity and click "Enhance" to enhance the current page.
</p>
<div class="screenshot">
<img src="firefox-extension/lang-topic-activity-enhance-restore.png" alt="VIEW toolbar with selections" />
</div>
<br/>
<p>
Click "Restore" to remove the activity.
</p>
<hr />
<p>
To have VIEW automatically enhance every page you load, click on the VIEW symbol
<img src="firefox-extension/toggle-off.png" alt="toggle VIEW" /> at the beginning of the toolbar.
</p>
<p>
Read more about the currently supported 
<a href="index.jsp?content=activities">topics and activities</a>.
</p>

</div>
